Figure 2 shows an example of a message flow for granting permissions to a sender device for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 3 shows an example of a message flow for initiating an invitation to a sender device for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 4 shows a representation of an example of a display on mobile device for managing permissions for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 5 shows a representation of an example of a display on mobile device for initiating an invitation to a sender device for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 6 shows a representation of an example of a display on mobile device for managing denied sender permissions for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 7 shows an example of a method of managing permissions for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver to a mobile device;
Figure 8 shows an example of a method of receiving a print document transfer request at a mobile device for transferring of electronic documents by a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 9 shows an example of a method of initiating an invitation to a sender device;
Figure 10 shows an example of a method of processing an invitation on a sender device to allow document transfer to a mobile device using a mobile device printer driver;
Figure 11 shows an example of a method of document transfer to a mobile device using a mobile device printer driver on a sender device; and
Figure 12 shows an example of a block diagram representation of a mobile device.

claim.claim-text:
A system comprising:
a mobile device (102/152) for receiving electronic documents (101), the mobile device (102/152) operable to associate a permission with a user identifier associated with the sending device (104);
a server (132) for locating the mobile device on a network (130);
a sending device (104) for sending documents (101) to the mobile device (102/152), the documents (101) transferred by a printer driver from within a document application on the sending device, the printer driver (109) providing formatting of the document (101) to be received by the mobile device (102/152), the client device (104) operable for sending a print permission request to the server (132) providing a user identifier associated with the mobile device and a user identifier associated with the sending device (102); and
the server (132) locating the mobile device (102/152) associated with the user identifier of the mobile device (102/152) and providing the print permission request to the mobile device (102/152), the mobile device (102/152) associating a permission with the user identifier associated with the sending device (104) and providing confirmation to the sending device (104) of acceptance of the print permission request, the sending device (104) adding a user identifier to the printer driver (109) for subsequent sending of documents (101) to the mobile device (102/152).
